What Happened to Instagram?
text:
Just have a look at the account @instagram and what content is being pushed forward. I just might be getting to old to understand the current wave of "creators" and their way of expression. Is this what people want to see?

As a photographer, designer and visual storyteller, I have a feeling that Instagram has become the opposite of what it was first intended to be and is not a place for us traditional creatives anymore.

Related to the topic, iGen: On the topic of narcissism and neuroticism, a great interview with Jordan Peterson and Dr. Jean Twenge: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8CJt2VwDuLE

text:

Looks like it prioritizes camera > no camera, but beyond that? Time talking, tone of voice, amount of responses?
